other_tests.findings: The appendix is dilated up to 1.4 cm, with a calcified appendicolith at the base of the appendix, significant fat stranding surrounding the appendix, but no drainable fluid collection or free air to suggest perforation. The small bowel and colon are within normal limits without evidence of wall thickening or dilatation. Various abdominal organs show no focal lesions or abnormalities.
